ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: I recognize that thoughts, behaviors, emotions, physiology, and situations are all interrelated
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: I track my mood and behavior to increase my awareness of the connection between them
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I feel down, I engage in activities that are enjoyable or give me a sense of accomplishment
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I am upset, I take time to identify what emotions I am feeling
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I have a negative emotional reaction, I identify what thoughts were just going through my mind
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I have a negative emotional reaction, I ask myself whether I am falling into  a thinking trap
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: I question my initial negative thoughts about a situation to develop a more balanced or alternative view
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: I am aware of underlying beliefs that fuel my negative emotions and affect the way I interpret situations
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: I collect positive evidence to develop new beliefs that are more balanced
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I notice a negative assumption or belief, I test it out with an experiment
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When my negative thoughts and emotions really bother me, I have a specific action plan of things I can do to cope
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I face difficult situations, I weigh my options, develop a solution, and follow through with the decision I made
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When facing interpersonal issues, I think through how to be assertive, anticipate obstacles I might encounter, and initiate conversations on the topic
Notes: 0 = not at all useful; 1 = somewhat useful; 2 = moderately useful; 3 = very useful; 4 = etremely useful; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: How useful: When I have a task that I might have trouble undertaking, I make and effort to break the task up into smaller parts
